Explanation:
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping in PrintingSchemaController, so the method-level request mappings are the full paths.
- The GET handler is declared with @RequestMapping(value = "/consumer/{consumerID}/printingschemas", method = RequestMethod.GET).
- The POST handler for the same path is declared with @RequestMapping(value = "/consumer/{consumerID}/printingschemas", method = RequestMethod.POST).
- PUT and DELETE handlers exist in this controller but target the different path "/consumer/{consumerID}/printingschemas/{printingSchemaID}", so they do not apply to the exact path requested.
- I based acceptability only on explicit RequestMapping annotations in the provided code (no assumptions about framework-provided implicit handling such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS behavior).
